  "conditionals": 50,
  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "Nitrogen catabolite repression in S. cerevisiae allows cells to preferentially use high-quality nitrogen sources (ammonia, glutamine) and repress genes for poor nitrogen utilization until needed. Under good nitrogen, TOR kinase activates, Gln3/Gat1 transcription factors are phosphorylated and cytoplasmic. Under nitrogen starvation, TOR inactivates, Sit4 phosphatase dephosphorylates Gln3/Gat1, they enter nucleus and activate NCR genes for alternative nitrogen sources (proline, urea, amino acids). The pathway integrates with GAAC (Gcn4) amino acid starvation response.",
  "id": "yeast_nitrogen_metabolism",
  "keywords": [
    "nitrogen catabolite repression",
    "NCR",
    "Gln3",
    "Gat1",
    "TOR",
    "nitrogen metabolism"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-15",
  "logicGates": {
    "and": 3,
    "not": 5,
    "or": 3
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    %% Nitrogen Source Detection\n    A[Nitrogen Sources] --> B{OR: Nitrogen<br/>Quality?}\n    B -->|Preferred - NH4+ Gln| C[Good Nitrogen]\n    B -->|Non-preferred - Pro Urea| D[Poor Nitrogen]\n    B -->|Starvation| E[No Nitrogen]\n    \n    %% TORC1 Activation\n    C --> F[Amino Acid Abundance]\n    F --> G[Gtr1/Gtr2 Rag GTPases]\n    G --> H[EGO Complex]\n    H --> I[TORC1 Recruitment to Vacuole]\n    I --> J[TORC1 Activation]\n    \n    J --> K[Sch9 Kinase Phosphorylation]\n    K --> L[Tap42-PP2A Phosphatase Active]\n    L --> M[Gln3 Phosphorylation]\n    M --> N[Gln3-Ure2 Complex Formation]\n    \n    %% Cytoplasmic Retention\n    N --> O{AND: Ure2<br/>Binding?}\n    O -->|No| P[Gln3 Nuclear Entry]\n    O -->|Yes| Q[Gln3 Cytoplasmic Retention]\n    Q --> R[/(NCR Genes Repressed)/]\n    \n    %% Nitrogen Starvation Response\n    D --> S[Poor Nitrogen Sensed]\n    E --> S\n    S --> T[TORC1 Inactivation]\n    \n    T --> U[Sch9 Dephosphorylation]\n    U --> V[Tap42-PP2A Inactivation]\n    V --> W[Sit4 Phosphatase Activation]\n    \n    W --> X[Gln3 Dephosphorylation]\n    X --> Y[Ure2 Dissociation]\n    Y --> P\n    \n    %% Gat1 Parallel Pathway\n    X --> Z[Gat1 Dephosphorylation]\n    Z --> AA[Gat1 Nuclear Entry]\n    \n    %% Nuclear Transcription Activation\n    P --> AB{AND: GATA Sites<br/>in Promoters?}\n    AA --> AB\n    AB -->|No| AC[/No Transcription/]\n    AB -->|Yes| AD[NCR Gene Activation]\n    \n    %% OR Gate: Which NCR Gene?\n    AD --> AE{OR: Which<br/>Gene Class?}\n    AE -->|Permeases| AF[GAP1 - General AA Permease]\n    AE -->|Proline| AG[PUT1/2 - Proline Utilization]\n    AE -->|Urea| AH[/DUR1,2 - Urea Degradation/]\n    AE -->|Allantoin| AI[DAL Genes - Allantoin Use]\n    AE -->|GABA| AJ[UGA Genes - GABA Catabolism]\n    \n    %% Permease Expression\n    AF --> AK[Gap1 Production]\n    AK --> AL[Broad Amino Acid Uptake]\n    AL --> AM[Nitrogen Acquired]\n    \n    %% Proline Utilization\n    AG --> AN[Put1 Proline Oxidase]\n    AN --> AO[Put2 P5C Dehydrogenase]\n    AO --> AP[Proline \u2192 Glutamate]\n    AP --> AM\n    \n    %% Urea Degradation\n    AH --> AQ[Dur1,2 Urea Amidolyase]\n    AQ --> AR[/Urea \u2192 2 NH3 + CO2/]\n    AR --> AM\n    \n    %% Allantoin Pathway\n    AI --> AS[DAL1-7 Enzymes]\n    AS --> AT[Allantoin \u2192 Urea]\n    AT --> AQ\n    \n    %% GABA Metabolism\n    AJ --> AU[UGA1-4 Enzymes]\n    AU --> AV[GABA \u2192 Succinate]\n    AV --> AW[Enter TCA Cycle]\n    AW --> AM\n    \n    %% Feedback to TORC1\n    AM --> AX{OR: Nitrogen<br/>Sufficient?}\n    AX -->|Yes| F\n    AX -->|No| AY[Continue NCR]\n    AY --> AE\n    \n    %% Rapamycin Treatment\n    I --> AZ{AND: Rapamycin<br/>Present?}\n    AZ -->|No| J\n    AZ -->|Yes| BA[/TORC1 Inhibited/]\n    BA --> T\n    \n    %% GAAC Integration\n    E --> BB[Uncharged tRNAs Accumulate]\n    BB --> BC[Gcn2 Kinase Activation]\n    BC --> BD[eIF2\u03b1 Phosphorylation]\n    BD --> BE[GCN4 Translation]\n    BE --> BF[Gcn4 Transcription Factor]\n    BF --> BG[Amino Acid Biosynthesis Genes]\n    BG --> BH([Amino Acid Synthesis])\n    \n    %% Quality Control\n    C --> BI[Preferred Pathway Active]\n    BI --> BJ[Efficient Growth]\n    BJ --> BK([Optimal Growth])\n    \n    %% Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style B fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style G fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style H fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style I fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style J fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style K fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style L fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style M fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style N fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style O fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style P fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Q fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style R fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style S fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style T fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style U fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style V fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style W fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style X fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style Y fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Z fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AA fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AB fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AC fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style AD fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AE fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style AF fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AG fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AH fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style AI fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AJ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AK fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style AL fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AM fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AN fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AO fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AP fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AQ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AR fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style AS fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AT fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AU fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AV fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AW fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AX fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style AY fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AZ fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style BA fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style BB fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BC fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BD fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BE fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BF fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style BG fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BH fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BI fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BJ fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style BK fill:#000000,color:#fff",
